snippet.textDisplay: In the fields of Vrindavan, Krishna, the dark and handsome god, grazing his cows. The sound of his flute is so beautiful that the gopis (milkmaids) are completely enchanted by it. They wonder where he will hide from them today.  In sand shore of Yamuna river, there is a Kadam tree, they want to tie him to it and beat the hell out of him. They keep asking, "Where will you hide today, oh, dark noughty god?"
